result.execSummary:
The defendant Jab T. Green was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misdemeanor Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Amendment to Judgment of Conviction
Restitution -0- None Requested
Notice of Hearing - Per USPS, Return to Sender - Not Deliverable As Addressed
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights with attachments.

(2:03 PM cases 21CM104, 21CM133, 21CM225, 21CM735, 21CM799, 22CM108, 22CF184, 22CF187 called.) All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Prosecuting attorney Robert W. Stoiber appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Jab T. Green appeared by video, in custody in the Eau Claire County Jail. Attorney George E. Miller appeared in court for Jab T. Green.
Victim/Witness statute complied with. Agreement has been reached and is recited by counsel.
Defendant waives right to a personal appearance and wants to proceed. Court accepts the defendant's waiver to a personal appearance.
Prior offense acknowledged for repeater enhancers.
Defendant pleads No Contest to 21CM104 Count 4: Domestic Misdemeanor Battery as Repeater, 21CM133 Count 4: Misdemeanor Bail Jumping as Repeater, 21CM735 Count 1: Misdemeanor Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) as Repeater, Count 6: Misdemeanor Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) as Repeater, 22CM108 Count 1: Misdemeanor Retail Theft - Intentionally Conceal (<=$500) as Repeater and 22CF187 Count 3: Misdemeanor Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) as Repeater.
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts the defendant's No Contest pleas and finds the defendant Guilty of 21CM104 Count 4, 21CM133 Count 4, 21CM735 Count 1, Count 6, 22CM108 Count 1 and 22CF187 Count 3.

Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on probation for 3 years with the following conditions:
Maintain absolute sobriety. AODA and follow through with recommendations. No contact with N.B., Kwik Trip, Fleet Farm, Menards. Restitution in the amount of $68.29 plus 5% and 10% surcharges in 21CM735 and restitution plus 5% and 10% surcharges to be determined in cases 22CM108 and 22CF187. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs to include 4 bench warrant fees in 21CM104. 21CM104 4 days credit if probation revoked. 21CM133 4 days credit if probation revoked. 21CM735 0 days credit if probation revoked. 22CM108 16 days credit if probation revoked. 22CF187 16 days credit if probation revoked. Any remaining charges including cases 21CM225, 21CM799, 22CF184 are dismissed and read in.
